solutions.content:
imagine the first round we can do x steps, x is min(26, k)
for each different char, we can change it to the destination char in the first round, after that, we have to always wait for another 26 times

for example, "ab" -> "cd"

'a' to 'c' needs 2 steps;
'b' to 'd' needs 2 steps;

but we can only do ONE replacing with 2 steps to make 'a' to 'c'
to make 'b' to 'd' happen, we will need to wait for next round, which is 2+26 = 28. 

so simply check how many cases(C) exist for a N steps operation.
if N + (c-1)*26 > K then we can't make it happen. 

```
bool canConvertString(string s, string t, int k) {
        if(s.size() != t.size())
            return false;
        if(s == t)
            return true;
        vector<int> times(26);
        int n = s.size();
        for(int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            int ti = (t[i] - s[i] + 26) % 26;
            ++times[ti];
        }

        for(int i = 1; i < 26; ++i) {
            if(i + (times[i] - 1) * 26 > k)
                return false;
        }

        return true;
    }
```

