```
/*

    actually here, the k value represents the maximum difference we can use
    to go from a to b - we can start from a and reach b in one step 
                      - we can start from a, complete a full circle, and come back to a, then take 1 step to reach b (1 + 26 steps)
                      - we can start from a, complete 2 full circles, and come back to a, then take 1 step to reach b (1 + 2*26 steps)
                      - if we take m circles then, we will take 1 + m*26 steps

   notice that to transform s[i] to t[i], the number of circles, we will have to take is the number of occurrences of the difference 
   (t[i] - s[i] + 26) % 26 [this is actually the circular difference between s[i] and t[i] (angular displacement*r)] 
   like if we want to convert x to a, then the shortest path in ciruclar fashion will be (a - x + 26) % 26 = (-23 + 26) % 26 = 3


   for example 
   a a b
   b b b

   for converting the first a to b, we used 1 step
   now for converting the second a to b, we will have to use the next available option : that is [1 + 1*26] = 27
