solutions.content:
1. If length( s ) and length( t ) are not equal, then it'll never be possible to convert, because we are not allowed to add or remove character from the strings. Hence ans = false.

We want to store remainder, as well as frequency into the map.
Ex.1. For 'a' to 'z' conversion, 'z' - 'a' = 25, Added with 26 and take mod 26, rem = (25+26)%26 = 25.
Ex.2. For 'z' to 'a' conversion, 'a' - 'z' = -25, added 26 and take mod 26, rem = (-25+26)%26 = 1.
So 26 is added to avoid negative remainder, as we are only allowed to move forword.

2. Ex.3. For s = 'aaab' to t = 'bbbb' conversion, we want three 'a' to 'b' conversion.
So, rem = ('b'-'a'+26)%26 = 1, frequency = 3.
for s[0] = 'a' to t[0] = 'b', we need 1st move, we use 1st move,
for s[1] = 'a' to t[1] = 'b', we need 1st move too, we use (1+(26\*1) ) = 27th move,
for s[2] = 'a' to t[2] = 'b', we need 1st move too, we use (1+(26\*2) ) = 53rd move,
Hence, if for a particular remainder frequency = 'x', we're gonna check, if '(x-1)\*26 + rem' belongs to the range [0, k] or not.
So, we directly check for 53 <= k, if not, then ans = false.

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canConvertString(string s, string t, int k) {
        unordered_map<int, int> mp;
        int n = s.size(), i, rem, freq;
        if( t.size() != n )return false;
        for( i = 0; i < n; i++ ){
            if( s[i] == t[i] )continue;
            rem = ( t[i] - s[i] + 26)%26;
            mp[rem]++;
        }
        for( auto& x : mp ){
            rem = x.first;
            freq = x.second;
            if( ( freq-1 )*26 + rem > k )return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```
