solutions.content:
Idea:

1. if the character is closing `)` 
	* stack is not empty
		 if last character in stack is also `)` then just pop two characters from stack `())`
		 else add character in stack
	* to make balance we need to insert `(` before so increment count and add `(` in stack along with `)`
2. if the character is closing `(` 
	* stack is not empty
		if stack peek is also `(` just add into stakc
		else count++ and pop from stack 
	*  add into stack

3. loop until stack is not empty and check 
	* if peek character `(` count += 2 and pop from stack once
	* else for `)` count++ and pop from stack twice


```
class Solution {
    public int minInsertions(String s) {
        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();
        int count = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == ')') {
                if (!stack.isEmpty()) {
                    if (stack.peek() == ')') {
                        stack.pop();
                        stack.pop();
                    } else {
                        stack.add(c);
                    }
                } else {
                    count++;
                    stack.add('(');
                    stack.add(c);
                }
            } else {
                if (!stack.isEmpty()) {
                    if (stack.peek() == '(') {
                        stack.add(c);
                    } else {
                        count++;
                        stack.pop();
                    }
                } else {
                    stack.add(c);
                }
            }
        }

        while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
            if (stack.peek() == '(') {
                count += 2;
                stack.pop();
            } else {
                count++;
                stack.pop();
                stack.pop();
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
}
```

