// Define balance such that '(' increments it by 2, and ')' decrements it by 1. 0 balance is expected at the end.
// if '(' comes, make sure balance is not an odd number, because then one opening parenthesis has only been partially closed. If balance is odd, we need to add ), and modify balance accordingly.
// if balance going negative, we have extra closing parenthesis. Add '(' and inc by bal by 2. 
// At the end, if balance>0, we need to add extra ')' to make balance=0.
```

