What we have done is:  we will use three numbers:(-1,0,1)
1. 1 number states that "))" substring is present.
2. 0 number states that only ")" substring is present and we need one more ')'.  
3. -1 number states that "(" is present.
4. Last we will have a variable "count" wich will store no of insertions.
*  If we encounter -1 "(", we will push it to the stack.
*  If we encounter 0 ")", this means we need to insert ")" so we will count++. But we will check if stack is empty, this means we need  to insert "(" also and we will again count++ and pop.
*  If we encounter 1"))", this means pop from the stack [or remove "("].

For eg [" ( )) ( )"]:- In this our array will be [-1,1,-1,0].
array[0]:First we will push -1 to stack.
array[1]:Then we will pop.
array[2]:Then we will push -1 to stack.
array[3]:Then we will count++ and pop.
Answer is 1.
