solutions.content:
* when s[i] == ')' && (s[i+1] == '(' or i == s.size()-1), we need to insert one ')'; Otherwise, there are two consecutive ')', and we skip the next one: i++
* when every time we face two ')', subtract one '(' and check if it is < 0. If yes, we need to insert one '(' and reset left to 0.
* after one time pass. res += left\*2 to make sure if there are not enough ')'.
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minInsertions(string s) {
        int res = 0, left = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); ++i) {
            if (s[i] == '(') {
                ++left;
            } else {
                if (i < s.size()-1 && s[i+1] == ')') {
                    ++i;
                } else {
                    ++res;
                }
                if (--left < 0) {
                    ++res;
                    left = 0;
                }
            }
        }
        return res + left*2;
    }
};
```

