solutions.content:
Here we are maintaining a stack of `')'`. But for that the size of stack is enough. We start from the end of the string.
If we encounter a `'('`, then we must subtract 2 from the stack. If less than 2 `')'` are available in the stack then we add the number of `')'` required to make it balanced i.e. `2 - (stack size)`.
If we encounter a `')'`, then we check if we have 2 consecutive `')'`. If yes, then we add 2 to the stack else we add 1 more to the result and 2 to the stack.
In returning the result we have,
`res` = computed answer
`stack/2` = In case we have a residue of `')'` left over in stack, so we add 1 for every 2 in the result.
** `stack%2?2:0` = In case we have an odd number of residue, then we add 2 to the result, 1 `'('` and 1 `')'`.
This last condition is not required because we are adding `')'` into the stack in sets of 2. So we wont have any odd number of parenthesis in the stack.
```
int minInsertions(string s) {
        int res = 0, stack = 0;
        for(int i=s.size()-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(s[i]=='('){
                if(stack<2)
                    res += 2-stack;
                stack = max(stack-2,0);
            }
            else{
                if(i>0 && s[i-1]==')'){
                    stack += 2;
                    i--;
                }
                else{
                    res += 1;
                    stack += 2;
                }
            }
        }
        return res + (stack/2); // + (stack%2?2:0);
    }
```

