# Missing Data
the opening bracket can only be balanced by pair of consecutive closing brackets. 
For example in the following case: 
(()))(()))()())))
See the following screenshot how the brackets are balanced with each other. Same color opening brackets will be balanced with first occurence of same color closing bracket towards it right.

![bracketsBalanced.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ce86266a-410c-4a01-872b-d3ebce631140_1695553126.7488647.png)


The answer should be 4
Explanation: 
The first red brackets need 1 closing bracket to balance. 
Similarly the next Green Brackets need one 1 closing bracket
Blue Brackets need 1 closing bracket 
Brown Brackets need 1 opening bracket

# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Keep count of opening bracket encountered so far, 
If the current bracket is an closing bracket, balance it with one of the opening bracket, if there is any otherwise, we just have to insert one opening bracket. 



# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ --> 
O(N)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minInsertions(String s) {
        int open, close, index ;
        open = close  = index = 0;
        while ( index < s.length()){
            char ch = s.charAt(index++);
            if ( ch == '('){
                open++;
            }
            else{
                // this is an closing bracket.
                if ( index >= s.length() || s.charAt(index) != ')'){
                    close ++;
                }
                else{
                    index++;
                }
                if ( open > 0){
                    open--;
                }
                else{
                    close++;
                }

            }
        }
        return close + open*2;

    }
}
```

