# Approach
declare two variables res(extra characters added) and stack(to keep track of open paranteses)
if we encounter a ( just add it to the stack.
if you encounter a )


then check the character after that there are three cases possible.
1. )  -two cases possible
    1.  empty stack first add a opening bracket  
    2. filled stack just reduce the stack by 1
2. (  -two cases possible
    1. empty stack add opening first then closing 
    2. add only closing and increase the stack by one
3. string get out of bounds- two cases possible similar to one just add extra )
    1.  empty stack first add a opening bracket  
    2. filled stack just reduce the stack by 1

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minInsertions(String s) {
        int res=0;
        int stack=0;
        int n =s.length();
        int i=0;
        while(i<n)
        {    char c = s.charAt(i);

            if(c=='(')
            {
                stack++;
                i++;
            }
            else
            {
                if(i<n-1 && s.charAt(i+1)==')')
                {
                    if(stack>0)
                    {
                        stack--;
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        // since no opening present add one 
                        res++;
                        stack++;
                        // since the second digit is ')' hence we will consume one opening bracket
                        stack--;
                    }
                }
                else if(i<n-1 && s.charAt(i+1)=='(')
                {
                    if(stack>0)
                    {

                        res++;
                        stack--;
                        // adding '(' to stack
                        stack++;
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        // since no opening present add one 
                        res++;
                        res++;
                        stack++;
                        stack--;
                        stack++;

                    }

                }
                else 
                {
                    if(stack>0)
                    {
                        res++;
                        stack--;
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        // since no opening present add one 
                        res++;
                        stack++;
                        // since the second digit is ')' hence we will consume one opening bracket
                        // since no second character is present adding one more ')'
                        res++;
                        stack--;
                    }
                }
                i=i+2;

            }

        }
         return 2*stack+res;
    }
}
