# Intuition
Using string only and wothout stack

# Approach
1. Create a new string and we will use it as a stack.
2. Check if string is not empty and it's top and string's current character's difference is 32, If it is, then pop_back.
3. else, just push_back it in the string.
4. Return the string.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string makeGood(string s) {
        string str = "";

        for(char ch : s){
            if( !str.empty() && (abs(str.back() - ch) == 32) ){
                str.pop_back();
            }else{
                str.push_back(ch);
            }
        }

        return str;

    }
};
```

