# Approach
Keep checking the difference between the last character in result and the `ith` character. The difference between the ASCII value of lower and upper case of same character is 32. 

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public String makeGood(String s) {
         // create result with empty string
        StringBuilder res = new StringBuilder();
        for (char ch : s.toCharArray()) {
            int resLength = res.length();
            // if the difference between the ith character of s
            // and last character in result is 32
            // then remove the last character from result
            // otherwise append the latest character to result
            if (resLength!=0 && Math.abs(res.charAt(resLength-1) - ch) == 32) {
                res.deleteCharAt(resLength - 1);
            } else {
                res.append(ch);
            }

        }
        return res.toString();
    }
}
